sources.data_found: DePaul University School of Computing 'High-Performance Compute Cluster' page states 'Coming Fall 2025' and mentions GPU acceleration with NVIDIA H100 NVL and A100 GPUs, but does not provide number of nodes, GPUs per node, or total GPUs.
DePaul 'AI Tools at DePaul' page lists enterprise AI services (e.g., Copilot Chat) but does not describe any on-prem GPU cluster hardware specifications or counts.

student_data.notes: Source is DePaul IRMA FactFile (Institutional Research & Market Analytics) Table 1-5: "Program Enrollments by College" with the header "Fall 2021/22 - Fall 2025/26" and columns labeled 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025. Using the 2024 column (Fall 2024 / AY 2024-2025): Undergraduate → Jarvis College of Computing and Digital Media → "Computer Science" = 845. Graduate → Jarvis College of Computing and Digital Media → "Computer Science" = 496 (MS/masters program enrollment). Graduate → Jarvis College of Computing and Digital Media → "Computer & Information Science" = 43 (PhD program enrollment). No explicit "last updated" date is shown on the page. [WARNING: Original source was inaccessible, using fallback.]

other_high_vram_gpus.notes: Mentioned as part of DePaul School of Computing 'High-Performance Compute Cluster' (Coming Fall 2025), but no public node/GPU counts (nodes, GPUs per node) are provided.
Mentioned as part of DePaul School of Computing 'High-Performance Compute Cluster' (Coming Fall 2025), but no public node/GPU counts (nodes, GPUs per node) or A100 40GB vs 80GB split are provided.

gpu_resources.notes: Clusters found with publishable specs (nodes and GPUs_per_node): none. The only DePaul-hosted page found referencing GPU cluster hardware (hpcc.cs.depaul.edu) provides GPU model families (H100 NVL, A100) but no counts, so nodes × GPUs_per_node totals cannot be computed. Therefore all requested GPU totals are set to 0 and the mentioned-but-unquantified GPUs are listed under other_high_vram_gpus with count=null.

analysis_notes: Data collected via multi-query approach: separate student and GPU searches.
validation_notes: No changes made. The GPU counts are already 0 due to lack of quantifiable data, and the student data is complete.
